te=PCWorld|publisher=IDG|accessdate=10 June 2016|date=27 January 2016}}</ref>\n| {{dts|2016-01-25}}\n|\n* It used Debian 8 as its base and included a new Gnome shell desktop environment, systemd, and a new installation process.<ref name=\"Paul-2016-01-27\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=3 | 2.0.1\n|-\n| {{Version | o | 2.2}}<ref name=\"Hoffman-2016-06-09\"/>\n| {{dts|2016-03-07}}\n|\n* Enabled viewing DRM-protected DVDs.<ref name=\"Hoffman-2016-06-09\"/>\n* Added a new \u201cOnion Circuits\u201d interface for viewing Tor routing information.<ref name=\"Hoffman-2016-06-09\"/>\n|-\n| colspan=3 | 2.2.1, 2.3\n|-\n| {{Version | o | 2.4}}<ref name=\"Hoffman-2016-06-09\">{{cite web|last1=Hoffman|first1=Chris|title=Tails, the anonymity-focused Linux distribution with deep Tor integration, reaches version 2.4|url=http://www.pcworld.com/article/3080525/linux/tails-the-anonymity-focused-linux-distribution-with-deep-tor-integration-reaches-version-24.html|website=PCWorld|publisher=IDG|accessdate=10 June 2016|date=9 June 2016}}</ref>\n| {{dts|2016-06-06}}\n|\n* Automatic account configuration of Icedove, harden kernel and firewall, update the DRM and Mesa graphical libraries.<ref name=\"version2.4\">{{cite web |url=https://tails.boum.org/news/version_2.4/index.en.html |title=Tails 2.4 is out |author= |website=Tails |date=2016-06-07 |accessdate=2016-06-07}}</ref>\n* New version of Tor Browser.<ref name=\"Hoffman-2016-06-09\"/>\n|-\n| {{Version | o | 2.5}}<ref name=\"version2.5\">{{cite web |url=https://tails.boum.org/news/version_2.5/index.en.html |title=Tails 2.5 is out |date=2016-08-02 |accessdate=2016-08-03 }}</ref>\n| {{dts|2016-07-31}}\n|\n|-\n| {{Version | o | 2.6}}<ref name=\"version2.6\">{{cite web |url=https://tails.boum.org/news/version_2.6/index.en.html |title=Tails 2.6 is out |date=2016-09-21 |accessdate=2016-09-22 }}</ref>\n| {{dts|2016-09-20}}\n|\n|-\n| {{Version | o | 2.7}}<ref name=\"version2.7\">{{cite web |url=https://tails.boum.org/news/version_2.7/index.en.html |title=Tails